<div id="review_21918685" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/21918685" />
    <a title="Caro" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/614156-caro"><img alt="Caro" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1195495127p2/614156.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/21918685?book_show_action=true">May 09, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Caro" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Caro" href="/user/show/614156-caro">Caro</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer21918685" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3160039201685450789">Entertaining to read, akin to the style of Edward Abbey or other 60&apos;s pop/outsider writing. The main character is oddly sympathetic even though he seems to be a sociopath, maybe. His ultimate motives are creative, if handicapped by serious psychological problems compounded by drugs. Interesting portrait of a mind *not* functioning well, told from the perspective of that mind! Plus a goofy story.<br/><br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText3160039201685450789" style="display:none">Entertaining to read, akin to the style of Edward Abbey or other 60's pop/outsider writing. The main character is oddly sympathetic even though he seems to be a sociopath, maybe. His ultimate motives are creative, if handicapped by serious psychological problems compounded by drugs. Interesting portrait of a mind *not* functioning well, told from the perspective of that mind! Plus a goofy story.<br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3160039201685450789" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
